Add Export feature with full per-breakpoint runtime adaptation

- New header button in DashboardPanel opens an Export modal with a live
  iframe preview, the source HTML in a textarea, and Copy / Download .html
  actions.
- New generator at client/src/lib/exportHtml.ts produces a self-contained
  HTML document (inline CSS, vanilla-JS countdown engine, Google Fonts
  link) that bakes in the current timer config. No React, no build step,
  drop-in ready.
- Per-breakpoint mode embeds all three full configs (desktop/tablet/mobile)
  in the script. The runtime picks the matching CFG via matchMedia at
  load and re-renders the body markup on resize when crossing
  breakpoints — so visible units, labels, header text, animation,
  progress style, completion behavior, and direction all adapt at each
  screen size, not just visual CSS. Visual styles continue to use
  mobile-first @media queries.
- Circular progress track stroke now uses `digitBackground` (matching
  the React CircularProgress component); bar uses `separatorColor`.
- Dynamic CMS mode falls back to a Fixed Date snapshot with a warning.
- Security: cssColor / cssFontFamily / cssNumber sanitizers guard every
  config-derived value interpolated into CSS; animationStyle,
  progressStyle, and direction are allow-listed before interpolation.
- Per-export FNV-1a hash is mixed into the evergreen localStorage key so
  multiple exported timers on the same domain do not collide.
- Same-tab redirect tries top-level navigation first, then falls back
  directly to window.open(url, "_blank") when sandboxed.
- Verified: typecheck clean, generator unit tests pass for single and
  per-breakpoint configs, browser screenshot at desktop width shows
  ticking flip clock with circular progress ring rendering correctly.
